Bid Documents
Request Future Documents
Specifications:
This is a modification to the existing firm fixed price (FFP) Financial Management Forms Automated Management Service (FMFAMS) IT Support Purchase Order, number FA701418P1006. This modification will increase the scope and magnitude of the service by allowing 40 additional financial systems to be on-boarded, which will result in an increase from the total contract value of by $26.7M from $8.6M to $35.3M. This modification will temporarily meet the Office of Under Secretary of Defense (OUSD) requirement to extend the FMFAMS IT support contract with the least amount of disruption to the current support. FMFAMS currently automates three key Financial Management Forms processes which are material for audit: (1) Appointment/Termination of Departmental Accountable Officials (DAOs), (2) Key Signatories (KS) of Financial Documentation; and (3) The System Authorization Access Request (SAAR) for FM information systems. FMFAMS currently has 13 FTEs and is only being utilized by the Air Force. This modification will increase the number of FTEs to 70+, and will allow the deployment of FMFAMS to the entire Department of Defense (DoD) enterprise.

Microsoft Enterprise Mail ExchangeBased on the requirements identified, BIDDER will work with LA-RICS to determine theend state Exchange design. After configuration, ADI users and groups willbe automatically added, changed and archived on the Active Directory. This will be aone-way process of synchronization.BIDDER is required to maintain the Client Access, which is the connection and supportbetween servers for software applications (e.g. Microsoft Outlook).BIDDER is required to configure and maintain the Compliance and Archiving rules. Thisprocess will move data that is no longer actively used to a separate storage area/devicefor long-term retention. Archive data consists of older data that remains important toLA-RICS and must be able to be retrieved at any time. BIDDER is required to configure and maintain the servers Transport role and rules.The Transport shall route internet email flow in and out as well as protect the emailsfrom viruses and spam.BIDDER is required to configure and maintain the Servers Storage, which shalloptimize the appliance to feed information to the user. The Storage is used to store,access, secure and manage digital data, files and services over the network.Task 3. Active DirectoryBIDDER is required to configure and maintain an Active Directory for the following:1. Set the rules for Schma, which will define the classes of objects and attributescontained in the directory.2. Maintain the Global Catalog, which contains information about every object in thedirector. This will allow users and administrators to find directory information inthe data.3. Configure and maintain the Query and Index Mechanism. This is so the objectsand their properties can be published and found by network users or application.4. Maintain the Replication Services, which distributes directory data across thenetwork.BIDDER shall consult the current Active Directory design and look for gaps ordeficiencies in the following areas:1. Forest and Domain Architecture2. Domain Controllers3. DNS and Namespace design4. NetBIOS Name Resolution5. Flexible Single Master Operation (FSMO) Placement6. Replication topology and Site Design7. Group Policy Objects8. AD DS Monitoring and Backup Processes9. AD DS Disaster Recover10. AD DS Antivirus; Patch Management Processes11. Security Policies12. Account Lockout PoliciesBIDDER shall work with LA-RICS to understand the current environment and plan outthe details for the new Microsoft environment within the constraints of the solution.Topics to be covered in this phase include:1. Verify that requirements are meta. Determine server naming conventionsa. Review of fully qualified domain name (FQDN), IP dependencies3. Identify existing Domain Services roles that will need transfers to the new domaincontrollers (DCs)a. DNS, DHCP, WINSb. Reuse of existing DCs NetBIOS names and/or IP Addressesc. Bid Alert No.:  0000229836
Agency Bid No.:  7102-20
Title:  Floodplain Partners: Flood Hazard Mitigation and Acquisition Pilot
Received Date:  01/16/2020
Close Date:  02/07/2020  10:00 AM
Purchase Type:  One Time Purchase
Delivery Date:  12/31/2020
Special Notices:  Questions due date: 01/24/2020 - Federally Funded, Insurance Required
Specifications:
Boulder County is seeking a qualified consultant to assist with the Floodplain Partners: Flood Hazard Mitigation and Acquisition Pilot ("Floodplain Partners Pilot"). The Boulder County Floodplain Management Program received a FEMA Flood Mitigation Assistance (FMA) advanced assistance grant to complete the pilot program. The goal of the Floodplain Partners Pilot is to determine if a community flood hazard mitigation program is desired by the community and if it is feasible for properties with significant flood risk within Boulder County to meet the eligibility requirements for the FEMA Flood Mitigation Assistance (FMA) grant programs. The pilot will include outreach to the community, identification and evaluation of up to 12 properties, and up to six FMA program grant applications. The consultant support included in this RFP includes site-specific evaluations, alternatives analysis, and conceptual design of mitigation strategies; support of FEMA Benefit-Cost Analyses; and FEMA FMA applications.

UNC is seeking proposals for the selection of a vendor to implement an electronic student success platform for supporting a case management approach for UNC's integrated network of student services. Case management facilitates access to mental health and substance abuse support, academic support and skill development, navigate university processes, managing finances, identifying and maintaining employment, engagement in campus and community activities, and facilitating social connections. This platform will be used by students, faculty and staff to house a students' profile and track their academic, conduct, career, and financial history with a focused effort on persistence and completion. The software must be able to prioritize student interventions according to levels of severity, automate and support outreach communications at various points in the semester. This product must integrate with current communication plans and allow for individual or group emails and texting capabilities. Multiple constituents at the University must be able to view each plan. It should have the capability to adapt to various mobile devices. There needs to be a "notes" section incorporated into the platform where various constituents can place comments on the progress of the student. The technology for this system must fully integrate with Ellucian Banner, Ellucian Degree Works, Ellucian ODS, Technolutions Slate, CBORD HMS/PCS and Instructure Canvas. Title:  Office Productivity Solution Migration (Office 365)
Received Date:  12/13/2019
Close Date:  01/22/2020  10:00 AM
Purchase Type:  One Time Purchase
Estimated Amount:  200000
Delivery Point:  Farmington Hill
Delivery Date:  Not Stated
Special Notices:  Prebid Conference Recommended 12/20/2019 02:00 PM - Questions due date: 01/07/2020 - Bid Bond 5% - Bid Deposit Required
Specifications:
It is the intent of the City of Farmington Hills, Michigan (herein referred to as "Farmington Hills" or "City") to solicit proposals from qualified Vendors whom can assist the City in the transition to the Microsoft Office 365 services as a means to streamline and optimize information sharing and collaboration. Therefore, it's important the City find a partner that is capable of assisting in all aspects of this transition. The City has determined the Office 365 migration shall begin with the email migration from their current GroupWise email system to Microsoft Office 365 Exchange services. The City also hosts email for the neighboring City of Farmington, Michigan (herein referred to as "Farmington"). This project scope encompasses the configuration of Office 365 tenant environments, the migration of users from both cities to individual Microsoft Office tenants, migration of email and calendar data, and the upgrade/deployment of the Office productivity software to all end user devices in both cities. The detailed specifications for the services associated with this project are described in section 2 of this RFP document. Farmington Hills reserves the right to award a contract or contracts that best meet the needs of Farmington Hills and the City of Farmington as it relates to accomplishing the objectives articulated in this RFP.

Bid Alert No.:  0000228048
Agency Bid No.:  RFP-419
Title:  Software Application for Planning, Permitting, Licensing, Housing, Constituency
Received Date:  12/10/2019
Close Date:  01/31/2020  02:00 PM
Purchase Type:  Term Contract: 1 year
Delivery Point:  City of Yonkers
Delivery Date:  Not Stated
Special Notices:  Questions due date: 01/03/2020 - Insurance Required, Training Required
Specifications:
Software Application for Planning, Permitting, Licensing, Housing, Constituency Services, and Asset ManagementThe City of Yonkers is seeking proposals from vendors or authorized resellers to supply and implement a Building and Housing Off-the-Shelf (OTS) software to satisfy the City of Yonkers business and technical requirements. The implementation of the software will be directly through the vendor or authorized partners who have high levels of experience with similar implementations in municipal government sectors. The majority of project work will take place at the City of Yonkers office in 87 Nepperhan Ave, Yonkers, NY.The City of Yonkers would like to leverage functionality within the software to replace and enhance functionality provided by existing systems as well as automate existing manual activities and minimize the number of applications required to facilitate its permitting, housing, licensing, and constituency services processes. The solution should support ensure efficient, best-in-class processes, maximizing the return on investment.The City of Yonkers is striving to utilize a single software solution to deliver on the planning, permitting, housing, licensing, constituency services, and asset management for these functional areas; Department of Housing and Buildings, Constituency Services, Engineering, and Planning. A high-level overview of each of these areas within scope is outlined below. However, it is important to note that if vendors determine that their solutions cannot meet all the requirements specified for the these areas, but can address the main area of Housing and Buildings, then only a proposal need be provided for that Housing and Buildings. In absence of a single software solution being able to satisfy all requirements (and where multiple software systems are required), the solutions to be utilized must be tightly integrated, permitting the automated transfer of data and synchronization as required, with appropriate data integrity checks.

SpecificationsThe City of Taylor is currently implementing a new ERP system using Oracle Cloud and NetSuite platforms. Related to this project, the City seeks to contract with a qualified vendor or vendors to provide Information Technology (IT) Professional Services related to data extraction and other services from the City's current ERP software to the new Oracle platform. The City currently uses New World IBM AS400/IBM iSeries. The successful firm would need knowledge of RPG and CL programming and DB2 data structure. Modules include building department inspections/permits, business licensing, council agenda system, payroll, death certificates, etcIn regards to the above project, the successful firm(s) will work with multiple City departments and representatives from Ciber HTC/GovSense (Oracle Agents) on a variety of programming functions necessary to ensure the successful migration and/or conversion of data from the old software (New World IBM AS400) to the new Oracle software platform. Below is a more extended list of services needed. Other services may be identified later.Data extracts from AS400 for all modules/departments that City be implementing in Oracle.For Example: Permit data, Plan Data, Water Billing, Utility Billing, etc.This data should include all the fields/information City wants to carry over to Oracle. (Fields would be things like Permit Type, Permit Expiration Data, Square Footage, etc. The firm will also need to assist Oracle with understanding the data model in the AS400.""Oracle will need a data dictionary of sorts, essentially explaining what the Field Name / Type in AS400 is (Example: pmt_typ = Permit Type)Once Oracle has the data above, they will then do the mapping, which may need assistance from the firm with the explanation of the fields.
